docs.abstract: The name change means consumers won’t mistakenly connect the Disney-owned studio with Mr. Murdoch’s polarizing Fox News.
docs.snippet: The name change means consumers won’t mistakenly connect the Disney-owned studio with Mr. Murdoch’s polarizing Fox News.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Sound the trumpets: 20th Century Fox, a name and klieg-lit logo that stretches back 85 years in Hollywood, is dropping the word Fox, a move that may prevent consumers from mistakenly thinking the movie studio has anything to do with Rupert Murdoch’s polarizing Fox News media empire.

headline.main: Disney Drops Fox From Names of Studios It Bought From Rupert Murdoch
headline.print_headline: Disney Drops Fox From Names of Film Studios

docs.abstract: The ride-hailing giant agreed to sell Uber Eats in India to rival Zomato, continuing its recent efforts to exit money-losing businesses.
docs.snippet: The ride-hailing giant agreed to sell Uber Eats in India to rival Zomato, continuing its recent efforts to exit money-losing businesses.
docs.lead_paragraph: MUMBAI, India — Uber, in its latest move to drop money-losing businesses, agreed on Tuesday to sell its food delivery business in India to Zomato, a local competitor, in exchange for 9.99 percent of the Indian start-up.

headline.main: Uber Sells Food Delivery Business in India
headline.print_headline: Uber Exits Food Delivery In India, Selling to Rival

docs.abstract: If the future lets people focus on work instead of driving during the daily commute, many of us will have to conquer motion sickness to read memos (or tweets). Researchers are working on some fixes.

headline.main: Avoiding Carsickness When the Cars Drive Themselves

docs.abstract: Jerome H. Powell is a pragmatist, and one who is quietly insulating an embattled Federal Reserve often in President Trump’s cross hairs.
docs.snippet: Jerome H. Powell is a pragmatist, and one who is quietly insulating an embattled Federal Reserve often in President Trump’s cross hairs.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Jerome H. Powell has spent much of his life toiling quietly behind the scenes, first as an investment banker and later as a governor at the Federal Reserve. Even as the central bank’s chair, and arguably the global economy’s most important figure, he has maintained a low-key image.

headline.main: How the Fed Chairman Is Shielding It From Trump
headline.print_headline: Chosen, Then Demonized, by Trump, Chair Quietly Insulates Fed

docs.abstract: The administration has said its North American trade pact would add 76,000 jobs in the sector. Experts are not so sure.
docs.snippet: The administration has said its North American trade pact would add 76,000 jobs in the sector. Experts are not so sure.
docs.lead_paragraph: In his State of the Union address in February, President Trump said the North American trade agreement his administration had negotiated would reverse the flow of auto manufacturing jobs by ensuring “that more cars are proudly stamped with our four beautiful words: Made in the U.S.A.”

headline.main: Unions Skeptical Trump’s Trade Deal Will Bring Back Auto Jobs

docs.abstract: The central bank suggested it would remain patient after cutting rates three times in 2019.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal Reserve officials left interest rates unchanged at their first meeting of 2020 on Wednesday, upholding their patient stance after an active, and often tumultuous, 2019.

headline.print_headline: Fed, Showing Confidence in Economy, Leaves Interest Rates Unchanged

docs.abstract: The ride-hailing company has faced questions about whether it can make money.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Lyft said on Wednesday that it was embarking on a corporate restructuring that would result in job cuts, as the ride-hailing company grapples with questions about whether it can make money.

headline.main: Lyft Plans Job Cuts as Part of Restructuring

docs.abstract: The president formally announced that he would nominate Judy Shelton and Christopher Waller to the Federal Reserve’s seven-person Board of Governors.
docs.snippet: The president formally announced that he would nominate Judy Shelton and Christopher Waller to the Federal Reserve’s seven-person Board of Governors.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Thursday said he would formally nominate Judy Shelton and Christopher Waller to the Federal Reserve’s Board of Governors, about six months after Mr. Trump said he intended to add the two to the central bank.

headline.main: Trump to Nominate a Critic and an Insider to the Fed Board
headline.print_headline: Trump Is Poised to Make Fed Critic and an Insider His Fed Board Nominees

docs.abstract: Borrowers whose schools abruptly shut down or used misleading practices won’t have to pay taxes on their forgiven balances.
docs.snippet: Borrowers whose schools abruptly shut down or used misleading practices won’t have to pay taxes on their forgiven balances.
docs.lead_paragraph: In a decision that will bring relief to tens of thousands of student loan borrowers, the Internal Revenue Service has expanded the pool of people who will not have to pay taxes on the balance of their forgiven loans.

headline.main: I.R.S. Exempts Some Forgiven Student Loans From Taxes
